HOW DO SCIENTISTS FIND FORMULAS--------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

FORMULAS:
A molecular formula tells exactly how many of each atom are in the molecule

An empirical formula tells the ratio of atoms in a molecule

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

HOW DO WE FIND AN EMPIRICAL FORMULA:

Divide all subscrripts in a molecular formula by the Greatest Common Factor.

Divide Molar mass of the molecule, by mass of empirca formula.

Multiply X by each subscript of the empirical formula. This will result in the 
molecular formula.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
